0":171,"351":167,"352":166,"353":273,"354":355,"355":421,"356":367,"357":413,"358":496,"359":214,"360":71,"361":74,"362":98,"363":67,"364":385,"365":294,"366":133,"367":109,"368":16,"369":115,"370":206,"371":121,"372":59,"373":220,"374":464,"375":17,"376":64,"377":137,"378":444,"379":12,"380":138,"381":193,"382":483,"383":40,"384":122,"385":520,"386":63,"387":65,"388":10,"389":104,"390":194,"391":75,"392":83,"393":126,"394":27,"395":107,"396":124,"397":199,"398":87,"399":360,"400":48,"401":106,"402":113,"403":85,"404":111,"405":201,"406":13,"407":296,"408":143,"409":81,"410":263,"411":145,"412":481,"413":38,"414":11,"415":86,"416":352,"417":90,"418":146,"419":208,"420":77,"421":9,"422":213,"423":28,"424":130,"425":362,"426":52,"427":125,"428":203,"429":92,"430":128,"431":363,"432":446,"433":210,"434":408,"435":409,"436":200,"437":417,"438":204,"439":25,"440":89,"441":8,"442":30,"443":348,"444":224,"445":195,"446":422,"447":519,"448":304,"449":451,"450":238,"451":335,"452":361,"453":256,"454":288,"455":462,"456":373,"457":465,"458":340,"459":4,"460":3,"461":6,"462":2,"463":403,"464":226,"465":101,"466":50,"467":123,"468":105,"469":140,"470":280,"471":497,"472":300,"473":239,"474":197,"475":192,"476":267,"477":212,"478":198,"479":512,"480":433,"481":150,"482":149,"483":61,"484":434,"485":82,"486":131,"487":19,"488":151,"489":466,"490":257,"491":486,"492":339,"493":298,"494":411,"495":270,"496":470,"497":258,"498":283,"499":44,"500":43,"501":242,"502":487,"503":322,"504":232,"505":259,"506":488,"507":429,"508":320,"509":310,"510":515,"511":22,"512":23,"513":479,"514":511,"515":58,"516":33,"517":326,"518":317,"519":299,"520":57,"521":372},"orderedDocs":[[24,"**1 minute before**"],[26,"**10 minutes before**"],[462,"**3 recurring threads** — things that show up across more than one day"],[460,"**300 frames** captured"],[459,"**5 days** captured"],[25,"**5 minutes before** (default)"],[461,"**60 distinct things** seen (people, files, sites, and so on)"],[210,"**A local provider keeps everything on your machine.** Connect Ollama or\nLM Studio and your text is processed locally, with no calls off the Mac."],[441,"**A local provider keeps everything on your machine.** Connect Ollama or\nLM Studio and your text is processed locally."],[421,"**A more responsive Mac while recording.** Day Journal capture pauses for the\nduration of a meeting, so screen capture and live transcription no longer\ncompete for the Neural Engine — and it resumes automatically when the meeting\nends."],[388,"**A new \"You\" tab.** A home for your profile: a short portrait of who you are, the traits\nit has noticed, and a timeline of how your days have felt."],[414,"**A page-peel turn.** Days now turn with a subtle page-peel animation instead\nof a flat slide. Honors Reduce Motion."],[379,"**A sidebar for the book.** An always-available table of contents. It auto-hides to give\nthe page room — hover the left edge to peek it open — or pin it from the toggle in the top-left."],[406,"**AI answers are now formatted.** Responses from Ask, the Second Brain, and\nmeeting Q\\&A render their Markdown — bold, italic, headings, and bullet lists —\ninstead of showing raw \"\\*\\*\" and \"\\*\" characters."],[288,"**AI vision descriptions.** Sends a downscaled, cropped screenshot of an\nactivity to a vision-capable model for a short visual description. A *local*\nmodel keeps the image on your Mac; a *cloud* model also requires the cloud\nconsent above."],[31,"**All events** — every timed event on your calendar."],[368,"**Always-on sidebar.** The book's Parts are visible by default on launch; unpin from the masthead toggle if you'd rather have the room."],[375,"**Answers from real content.** Ask \"why do I keep working with this client?\" and the chat reads\nthe actual text of the relevant moments — emails, docs, messages — and grounds its answer\nin them, with citations you can click to jump straight to the frame."],[165,"**Apple Silicon** (M-series). The on-device speech model runs on the Neural\nEngine, so an Apple Silicon Mac is required."],[487,"**Areas** — clusters Hindsight detected in the graph."],[243,"**Ask** — put a question to an AI provider about the conversation as it\nhappens (see below)."],[23,"**At start time**"],[511,"**Automatically check for updates** — on by default. Hindsight checks daily."],[512,"**Automatically download updates** — when on, a found update is fetched in the\nbackground so it is ready to install. This is available only while automatic\nchecks are on."],[108,"**Capture focused text (deep read)** reads the focused window's text through\nAccessibility for richer recall. It's off by default, stays on-device, and\nruns through the same redaction gate as everything else. Turn it on under\n**Settings → Capture** if you want it."],[439,"**Capture, transcription, and storage stay local.** Meetings are transcribed\non your Mac with the on-device speech model (Parakeet, which runs on the Neural\nEngine), and your journal database never leaves it."],[208,"**Capture, transcription, and storage stay local.** Meetings are transcribed\non your Mac, and your journal database never leaves it."],[394,"**Clearer meetings.** The section is consistently called \"Meetings\", larger calls\nget more distinct speaker colors, the connect-calendar prompt refreshes after you\ngrant access, and a failed prompt now shows an error instead of doing nothing."],[423,"**Clearer Screen Recording setup.** When Hindsight is opened from outside your\nApplications folder — where macOS runs it from a temporary, locked-down copy —\nsetup now tells you to move Hindsight to Applications and reopen it, which is\nthe only way the Screen Recording permission will stick. Previously it pointed\nyou at the \"+\" button, which can't take effect in that case."],[245,"**Click** the pill to open the panel."],[442,"**Cloud is opt-in.** Sending anything to a cloud provider is off until you\nturn it on, and the same gate applies uniformly to journal text, meeting\ntranscripts, chat, and drafts."],[211,"**Cloud is opt-in.** Sending your journal to a cloud provider is off until you\nexplicitly turn it on, and the same gate applies uniformly to journal text,\nmeeting transcripts, chat, and drafts."],[276,"**Cloud providers are gated by consent.** A cloud provider (Anthropic, OpenAI,\nGoogle Gemini, OpenRouter) is only allowed to receive your data after you turn\non **Allow cloud AI to analyze your journal**, which is **off by default**."],[516,"**Colophon → The Apparatus → Check for Updates…**"],[315,"**Colophon** — any setting, landing on its own row."],[316,"**Commands** — actions you can run, like Turn to today or Begin minutes."],[313,"**Commonplace Book** — beliefs you've kept."],[107,"**Context.** The app and window in front, so activities are easy to make sense\nof later."],[413,"**Day navigation works again.** The left/right arrow keys (and ⌘\\[ / ⌘]) turn\nbetween days without having to click the page first, and the optional\ntwo-finger swipe (Colophon → \"Turn pages with a two-finger swipe\") is reliable."],[135,"**Days/** — one note per captured day, with the day's narrative, a timeline of\nwhat you worked on, and linked lists of the **People**, **Links**, and **Files**\nseen that day. Your own notes for the day come along too. Each note carries\nfrontmatter (`date`, `captures`, `tags`)."],[383,"**Dismiss sticks.** When you dismiss something the Second Brain inferred about you, it\nno longer quietly comes back the next day."],[326,"**Emails**"],[142,"**Export graph (GraphML + Mermaid)** writes your knowledge graph — the people,\nsites, and files that recur together — in two visualization-ready formats:"],[500,"**Export graph** — your knowledge graph as GraphML (for yEd, Gephi, Obsidian)\nand Mermaid (for Markdown)."],[499,"**Export Obsidian vault** — daily notes with backlinked people, sites, and\nfiles."],[132,"**Export Obsidian vault** writes your whole journal as a folder of linked\nMarkdown notes — the kind of vault Obsidian, Logseq, or any plain-Markdown editor\ncan open directly."],[57,"**Export** supports several formats with `--format`: `txt` (default),\n`markdown`, `srt`, `vtt`, and `json`. By default the file is written as\n`<title>.<ext>` in the current directory; use `--output <path>` to choose the\nname, or `--stdout` to print instead of writing a file."],[289,"**External agents (MCP).** Lets an external AI agent query your journal\nlocally. It exposes only the structured, already-redacted recall — people,\nfiles, links, and graph — never screenshots. Exposing raw screen text\n(full-text search) is a separate, extra opt-in, and turning the agent server\noff revokes it."],[400,"**Far better speaker separation.** A one-on-one call is no longer split into a\nhandful of phantom speakers, and genuine group meetings keep everyone — the\nspeaker count is no longer capped, so a large call isn't truncated down to a\nfew voices."],[328,"**Files**"],[466,"**Files** — file paths and named files (matched against an extension list, so\n`roadmap.swift` is recognized but `v1.2` is not)"],[138,"**Files/** — one note per file, backlinked to the days it appeared."],[426,"**Fixed a launch crash on some Macs.** The bundled Daybook fonts failed to\nload on Macs other than the one the app was built on, which could crash\nHindsight at startup. Fonts now load reliably on every Mac."],[148,"**Graph files** — `~/Library/Application Support/Hindsight/GraphExport/`"],[143,"**graph.graphml** — open it in yEd,\nGephi, or Obsidian's graph plugins for an interactive,\nlaid-out view."],[144,"**graph.mermaid** — a Mermaid `graph TD` diagram you\ncan paste straight into Markdown, Obsidian, or Notion, or render at\nmermaid.live."],[140,"**GRAPH\\_REPORT.md** — a map-of-content for the vault: your most-connected\nnodes, surprising connections, and a few questions worth exploring, all\nresolving to the notes above."],[520,"**Help → Hindsight Help** or **Help → View on GitHub** opens the project on\nGitHub: github.com/iannellomarco/hindsight-next."],[515,"**Hindsight → Check for Updates…** in the menu bar, or"],[372,"**Honest about what vision sees.** The vision setting and the on-day redaction badge now say plainly: captured text is scrubbed, but visible pixels sent for descriptions are not."],[226,"**Hotkey** — press ⇧⌘M from anywhere. The same shortcut stops the\nrecording when you're done."],[483,"**How your picture has changed** — the arc of how the Second Brain's\nunderstanding of you has shifted over time."],[271,"**Insights, Network, and beliefs.** These are computed deterministically from\nyour own history on-device, so they work with no AI provider connected at all."],[386,"**It knows you.** Tell it your name and role (during setup, or anytime in Settings) and\nit speaks to you personally — greeting you by name and writing your day as someone it\nactually knows."],[376,"**It knows you're not your own coworker.** The Second Brain no longer lists you among the\npeople you work with."],[387,"**It learns you.** From your own days it quietly works out things like your role, the\nway you work, and how you've been feeling — and asks you to confirm the important guesses\nbefore trusting them. Nothing is assumed, and anything that feels off is one tap to dismiss."],[122,"**Journal database** (text, timeline, narratives, notes):\n`~/Library/Application Support/HindsightNext/hindsight.db`"],[363,"**Keyboard tabs in meetings.** Switch a meeting's Transcript / Results / Chat / Speakers with `⌘1`–`⌘4`, matching the rest of the app."],[314,"**Lexicon** — corrective words and snippets."],[327,"**Links**"],[137,"**Links/** — one note per web address you returned to, backlinked to the days\nit appeared."],[360,"**Local AI now grounds on the real thing.** When you use an on-device provider (Ollama, Apple Foundation Models, or LM Studio), Hindsight no longer strips contact details from what the model sees — names, emails, and phone numbers are preserved so your Second Brain and chat answers reference real people and projects instead of `[REDACTED:name]`. Nothing leaves your Mac, so there's no privacy cost. Secrets (cards, keys, tokens) are still scrubbed for every provider."],[275,"**Local providers keep everything on your Mac.** Connect a local model runner\n(Ollama, LM Studio, oMLX, or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint on `localhost`)\nand your text is processed on your machine, with no calls off the Mac."],[164,"**macOS 14.2 or later.**"],[361,"**Meeting chat speaks up when it fails.** A question to a meeting that can't reach the AI provider now shows the reason inline, instead of going silent or leaving a placeholder message behind."],[391,"**Meeting status updates instantly.** The menu-bar recording glyph, the permission\nprompt when a recording is blocked, and the \"transcribing…\" indicator now reflect\nwhat's happening the moment it changes."],[269,"**Meeting transcription.** Meetings are transcribed by an on-device speech\nmodel. Audio never leaves your Mac."],[420,"**Meetings wait for the speech model.** If you start recording before the\non-device speech model has finished its one-time setup, Hindsight now shows\n\"Preparing speech model…\" and begins once it's ready, instead of recording a\nmeeting that comes back with an empty transcript."],[227,"**Menu bar** — click the Hindsight status item and choose **Start Recording**."],[232,"**Microphone + System Audio** (default) — records your voice and the call\ntogether."],[312,"**Minutes** — a recorded meeting, by title."],[409,"**More accurate speakers.** Tightened speaker separation so a single remote\nparticipant is no longer occasionally split into two, and a slow\nspeaker-detection step no longer holds up the final transcript."],[485,"**Most connected** — the hubs your work threads through."],[392,"**Much better VoiceOver support.** Buttons and controls across the app — Meetings,\nthe Day Journal, the Second Brain, onboarding, and the Index — now announce\nmeaningful names, and secondary text meets WCAG AA contrast."],[237,"**Mute / Unmute** the microphone (mic + system mode only). Muting also pauses\nlive transcription of your voice."],[403,"**Name a meeting from your calendar.** One click names a meeting after the\ncalendar event it overlaps, so your recordings match your schedule."],[415,"**New app icon.** A Daybook cover with the rubric-red ribbon bookmark."],[398,"**New days appear right away.** After you stop and save a day, it now shows up\non the Days page immediately — previously a freshly finished day could stay\nhidden there until you quit and reopened the app."],[209,"**No AI traffic without a provider you choose.** If you don't connect an AI\nprovider, nothing is sent anywhere — Ask the book and the Second Brain simply\nwait until one is configured."],[440,"**No AI traffic without a provider you choose.** Until you connect an AI\nprovider, nothing is sent anywhere — Ask the book and the Second Brain simply\nwait."],[417,"**No more waiting to record.** Previously, starting a meeting could pause on\n\"Preparing speech model…\" while the on-device model loaded. Now recording\nbegins immediately and captures audio from the first second; the speech model\nloads in the background."],[274,"**No provider, no traffic.** If you haven't configured a provider, features\nthat use AI — Ask the book, Second Brain chat, drafting — simply wait. Nothing\nis sent anywhere."],[429,"**Notarized and stapled.** The app is signed, notarized by Apple, and the\nnotarization ticket is stapled into the build. macOS can verify Hindsight\noffline, so the first launch is clean even without a network connection — no\nspurious \"damaged\" or \"cannot be opened\" warnings."],[241,"**Notes** (default) — type your own notes as the meeting runs. They're saved\ncontinuously. An **Insert** menu adds quick snippets like `/decision`,\n`/action`, and `/question`."],[19,"**Notify before meetings** — a quiet note slips in before each meeting begins.\nNothing records on its own."],[147,"**Obsidian vault** — `~/Library/Application Support/Hindsight/ObsidianVault/`"],[18,"**Off** — Hindsight ignores your calendar. This is the default."],[106,"**On-screen text (OCR).** Each frame is read on-device so its text is\nsearchable and recallable. Recognition runs entirely on your Mac."],[362,"**One Send, everywhere.** The ask boxes in the meeting panel, meeting detail, and journal chats now share the same look and the same Send control — a consistent composer across the whole app."],[238,"**Pause / Resume** — pausing stops capture without leaving a gap; the saved\naudio plays back seamlessly."],[115,"**Pause when idle** stops capturing when you step away. On by default, after\n**2 minutes** idle (you can choose 30 seconds, 1, or 2 minutes)."],[465,"**People** — email addresses, and recurring phone numbers"],[136,"**People/** — one note per person, built from the email addresses in your\nhistory. Addresses are humanized into names (`jane.smith@example.com` becomes\n*Jane Smith*), and OCR variants of the same address collapse into a single\nnote. Each note lists the days that person showed up."],[325,"**Phone numbers**"],[389,"**Private by default.** All of this stays on your Mac and works with on-device AI. Sharing\nyour profile with a cloud provider takes a separate, explicit opt-in."],[468,"**Projects and tickets** — issue references like `#318`"],[401,"**Re-analyze a meeting.** A new button on a saved meeting re-runs transcription\nand speaker detection on the original audio — so you can pick up these speaker\nimprovements on meetings recorded earlier, without recording again."],[395,"**Rebindable meeting hotkey.** The global start/stop shortcut (default ⌘⇧M) can now\nbe changed in Settings → The Minutes."],[225,"**Record tile** — open the **Meetings** page (or the daybook's Today page)\nand click **Record** on the \"Record a meeting\" tile."],[367,"**Recoverable deletions.** Deleting a day now removes it from the book but offers an *Undo* right after, from Today — so a mistake never costs you a captured day."],[116,"**Reduce work on battery** lightens capture and analysis on battery power.\nOff by default."],[404,"**Refreshed meeting tabs.** The Transcript / Results / Chat / Speakers tabs now\nuse the same thumb-tab style as the rest of the app."],[188,"**Relaunch Hindsight.** macOS only applies this permission when the app\nstarts, so the status may keep reading *Not granted* until you quit and\nreopen. Setup will prompt you to relaunch if it notices the grant hasn't\ntaken effect yet."],[402,"**Rename a meeting.** A pencil next to the title renames a meeting at any time."],[252,"**Rename** it from the title."],[369,"**Richer timeline.** Every activity row now shows a thumbnail you can click to open full-size — not just the starred moments."],[246,"**Right-click** for **Stop**, **Pause / Resume**, **Open**, and **Cancel**.\nCancel discards the recording and deletes its audio, so it asks you to confirm\nfirst."],[255,"**Save Audio** to export the recording."],[268,"**Screen capture and OCR.** The Day Journal periodically captures your screen\nand reads it with on-device OCR. Screenshots are processed and stored locally\nand never uploaded."],[121,"**Screenshots:** `~/Library/Application Support/HindsightNext/journal`"],[105,"**Screenshots.** A frame of your front window, taken on-device at your chosen\ncadence. The default is **every 2 minutes** (you can pick 30 seconds, 1, 2, 5,\nor 10 minutes)."],[371,"**Secret-bearing frames never leave your Mac.** If a screenshot's captured text revealed a card, key, or token, its pixels are no longer sent to a vision provider — the text redactor can't see into the image, so the whole frame is withheld."],[384,"**Sharper recall.** Asking about a specific person or file now surfaces the right ones\nto jump to, instead of coming up empty on a normally-worded question."],[467,"**Sites** — web addresses, kept specific (`github.com/example/widgets` is its\nown thing, not collapsed into a bare `github.com`)"],[396,"**Smaller fixes.** Onboarding scrolls on small displays, the meeting audio player\nresets at the end of a clip, deleting a custom word asks first, and a failed app\nsummary can be retried."],[427,"**Smoother Screen Recording grant.** After you allow Screen Recording, setup\nnow shows a clear **Relaunch Hindsight** step — macOS only applies this\npermission to a freshly launched app, so the relaunch is what makes the grant\ntake effect."],[393,"**Snappier reading.** Opening a finished day, searching the Index, and reading\nstreamed answers are all faster and smoother."],[20,"**Start recording automatically** — Hindsight shows a 5-second cancellable\ncountdown, then begins the minutes."],[430,"**Steadier installs.** Hardened the DMG so dragging Hindsight to Applications\nand opening it the first time just works."],[239,"**Stop** — ends the meeting and starts transcription."],[424,"**Sturdier packaging.** The disk image is now signed unambiguously, and the\ndiagnostics behind the Screen Recording grant were tightened so first-run\nsetup issues are easier to trace."],[486,"**Surprising connections** — strong links between things that aren't both\ncentral, ranked by how many times more often than chance they appear together."],[233,"**System Audio Only** — captures just what's playing on your Mac, with no\nmicrophone. Use this for recordings where your own voice isn't needed."],[366,"**The Day Index.** Press `⌘L` anywhere to open a chronological overview of every captured day — title, date, and a thumbnail for each, with a density strip showing how much history you've built. Use `↑↓` to move and `Return` to turn straight to a day."],[311,"**The Days** — any page in your Day Journal, by title, summary, or date."],[181,"**The Index** — ⌘K goes anywhere: days, minutes, settings."],[182,"**The Ribbon** — the red mark always brings you back to today."],[377,"**Tighter privacy at the edge.** When a cloud model is in use, email addresses and phone\nnumbers are scrubbed from what's sent — on top of the existing secret redaction."],[380,"**Timeline previews.** Each moment in a day's timeline now shows a thumbnail you can click\nto open full-size."],[187,"**Toggle Hindsight on.** On recent macOS there's no confirmation dialog —\nflipping the toggle is the grant."],[469,"**Topics** — recurring subjects that tie the above together"],[139,"**Topics/** — \"area\" notes for the clusters Hindsight detected in your graph,\neach linking its members."],[242,"**Transcript** — the live, speaker-labeled transcript. Toggle **Auto-scroll**\nor **Copy** the text so far."],[408,"**Transcription no longer freezes.** A scheduling deadlock could leave the live\ntranscript blank during a meeting and the post-recording \"transcribing…\" step\nstuck indefinitely. Recording and transcription now run on separate lanes — the\nlive transcript fills in during the meeting and the final transcript completes\npromptly."],[180,"**Turn** — the left and right arrows move between days."],[411,"**Visible page controls.** The Days page now has previous / next buttons and a\ndotted day indicator beneath it — one dot per day, with the current day\nhighlighted. Click any dot to jump straight to that day. (The page-turn\ncontrols were previously invisible edge zones.)"],[418,"**Visible transcription progress.** While the model loads, the transcript area\nshows a progress bar instead of a frozen screen, and the transcript fills in as\nsoon as the model is ready. The full meeting is always transcribed when you\nstop."],[30,"**With participants** — any event that has at least one other attendee."],[29,"**With video link** (default) — only events that carry a recognized\nconference link. Hindsight detects Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, Webex,\nAround, and Whereby, plus other common meeting URLs."],[482,"**Worth confronting** — a frank, grounded mirror of things your own history\nsuggests, each shown with its evidence. This stays silent unless your tone dial\n(in the Colophon) allows it, and it never fabricates a criticism."],[481,"**Worth noticing** — patterns rising or cooling across your recent days. Each\nhas a quick action to draft an email or a follow-up calendar event from it."],[488,"**Your graph** — an interactive node-and-link canvas you can open with **Show\ngraph**."],[270,"**Your journal and graph.** The journal database, the people, files, sites,\nand beliefs in the Second Brain, and your meeting library are all stored on\nthis Mac."],[78,"`--base-url` — an absolute `http(s)` URL for self-hosted endpoints."],[79,"`--command` — the subprocess template, required for the `cli` provider."],[66,"`--diarize` — separate speakers and label each turn (Speaker 1, Speaker 2, …).\nTune with `--diar-threshold` (default `0.6`; lower finds more speakers) and\n`--diar-max-speakers` (default `6`)."],[81,"`--dry-run` shows the per-table counts (imported, skipped, unsupported) without\nwriting anything. Add `--json` for a structured report."],[62,"`--engine` — `parakeet` (default), `whisper`, or `app-default` (use whatever\nengine the app is set to)."],[64,"`--format` — `text` (default), `transcript` (timestamped lines), or `json`."],[63,"`--language` — language hint for Whisper, e.g. `en`, `it`."],[77,"`--model` — pick a model. Required for `openaiCompatible`, `lmstudio`, and\n`omlx`; other providers fall back to a conservative default."],[67,"`--no-save` — transcribe without adding the result to your library."],[65,"`--processing` — `raw`, `clean`, or `app-default` (default; follows your\nVocabulary setting). `clean` rebuilds punctuation and applies your custom\nwords."],[85,"`0` — success."],[86,"`1` — a runtime failure (network, provider, transcription, and similar)."],[87,"`2` — user misuse: bad arguments, a missing input file, or a lookup that was\nambiguous or too short."],[352,"1.0.0"],[351,"1.0.1"],[342,"1.0.10"],[341,"1.0.11"],[340,"1.0.12"],[350,"1.0.2"],[349,"1.0.3"],[348,"1.0.4"],[347,"1.0.5"],[346,"1.0.6"],[345,"1.0.7"],[344,"1.0.8"],[343,"1.0.9"],[339,"1.1.0"],[338,"1.1.1"],[337,"1.2.0"],[336,"1.3.0"],[335,"1.3.1"],[157,"1\\. Welcome"],[158,"2\\. Set up the Day Journal"],[159,"3\\. Microphone access (optional)"],[160,"4\\. Prepare on-device models"],[161,"5\\. Three moves, one rehearsal"],[162,"6\\. Ready"],[103,"A **MOMENTS** count. Press **Mark Moment** to flag something worth\nremembering as it happens; you can add a short note to a moment, too."],[101,"A **RECORDING** indicator with an elapsed clock."],[475,"A belief needs to show up across **at least two days** before it forms."],[381,"A bigger delete control, and clearer labels distinguishing asking the whole book from\nchatting with a single day."],[390,"A broad polish pass: more reliable meeting status, far wider accessibility, and a\nfaster, more consistent interface."],[445,"A few gigabytes of free disk space for the speech model, which downloads once\nduring first-time setup."],[166,"A few gigabytes of free disk space for the speech model, which downloads once\nduring setup."],[474,"A few things keep the picture stable and honest:"],[478,"A file or ticket you touched a couple of times and then dropped about a week\nago is flagged as an **open loop**, phrased as a possibility rather than a\nfact."],[397,"A fix so a finished day always shows up where you expect it."],[436,"A floating pill and a live panel with **Notes**, a speaker-labeled\n**Transcript**, and an **Ask** tab."],[405,"A formatting hotfix for AI answers."],[307,"A note on where this runs"],[428,"A packaging release focused on a smoother, more reliable first launch."],[438,"A page that reads across every day you've captured, links the things that keep\nrecurring, and forms plain-language **beliefs** about your focus. It moves\nbetween **Chat**, **Insights**, **Network**, and **Export**. The beliefs,\nInsights, and Network are computed locally and work with no AI provider\nconnected; recall grounds every chat answer in your real history with citations\nback to the moment each claim came from."],[172,"A quick tour of what Hindsight is: a **Day Journal** woven from periodic screen\ncapture, on-device meeting recording, and a design that keeps your data on this\nMac. Press **Get Started**."],[370,"A real privacy hardening for AI vision:"],[290,"A related option, **AI refinement of the self-model**, is on by default once a\nprovider is configured. It lets the connected AI tidy your beliefs and topics;\nturn it off to keep the plain, deterministic Second Brain. Like everything else,\nit only uses the provider you chose, under the same gate."],[419,"A reliability release for meeting recording — especially your first one after\ninstalling."],[102,"A running **FRAMES** count (screenshots taken so far)."],[433,"A running record of your day, woven from periodic screen capture read with\non-device OCR (Apple Vision). Turn between days with the left and right arrows,\nlet the red Ribbon bring you back to today, and use **Ask the book** on any page\nto pose a question about your day or your history. Screenshots and the journal\ndatabase never leave your Mac."],[251,"A saved meeting keeps its transcript, your notes, and any Ask conversation. You\ncan:"],[477,"A single quiet day can't retire a belief — it fades only after several quiet\ndays in a row."],[422,"A small reliability release for first-run setup."],[359,"A smarter privacy boundary for on-device AI — and a more consistent feel throughout."],[111,"After **Stop & Review**, Hindsight writes up your day and then opens a short\n**review** at the foot of today's page. It's a chat: it shows the running\nsummary, may ask a few follow-up questions to fill in gaps, and lets you add\nnotes. When you're happy, keep the day; or discard it. A kept day is saved as a\nfinished page you can turn back to anytime."],[220,"After a meeting"],[149,"After an export runs, a **Reveal in Finder** button appears next to it — the\nquickest way to jump to the files. The status line below the buttons confirms\nwhat was written (for example, &#x2A;Exported 12 days · 34 people · 18 links · 9\nfiles.* for the vault, or *Exported graph · 60 nodes · 142 edges* for the graph)."],[261,"AI is opt-in"],[291,"All of these settings live in **the Colophon**, Hindsight's settings page. Open\nthe Index with ⌘K and choose **Colophon**, then go to the\n**Intelligence** section."],[373,"And a sweep of reliability and polish: the recording control no longer lets *Discard* look like the main action; a failed Second Brain question now tells you instead of hanging; the \"relaunch to apply Screen Recording\" state stays visible until you act on it; a new multi-step progress bar in setup; and consistent ask fields, status dots, and delete confirmations throughout."],[40,"Any change you make takes effect immediately. Switch back to **Off** and\nHindsight stops watching your calendar entirely — a disabled feature does no\nwork in the background. Adjust your lead time, filter, or excluded calendars and\nthe next reminder or countdown follows the new rules. If a countdown is on\nscreen when you change a setting, it closes."],[112,"Any finished day also has **Chat with this day** — a free-form conversation\nabout that single day, answered from what was captured."],[281,"API keys"],[444,"Apple Silicon (M-series) — the on-device speech model runs on the Neural\nEngine."],[109,"As the day goes on, Hindsight periodically reviews the new screenshots and keeps\na running summary of what you've been working on. The default is **every 30\nminutes** (you can choose 15, 30, or 60). When you stop, that work becomes the\nday's narrative — a short, readable write-up that sits on the finished day's\npage alongside a timeline of your activities, the apps you used, your marked\nmoments, and any notes you add."],[464,"As you work, Hindsight reads the captured text on each page and pulls out the\nconcrete, recall-worthy things in it:"],[219,"Ask during a meeting"],[249,"Ask needs an AI provider; recording and transcription work without one.\nConnect a provider under **Settings → AI Provider** — a local provider keeps\neverything on your Mac."],[302,"Ask the Book: a question across every day"],[300,"Ask your book a question and get an answer drawn from your own days and meetings, with a link back to the exact moment it came from."],[306,"Asking about a single meeting"],[504,"Automatic updates"],[282,"Bearer tokens"],[278,"Before any text is sent to a provider, Hindsight runs an offline,\non-device pass that scrubs secrets out of it. This runs both at capture time\n(before anything is written to your journal) and again before every outbound AI\ncall. It recognizes:"],[129,"Before you export"],[179,"Before you finish, Hindsight has you rehearse the three ways you move through\nyour book:"],[330,"Before you've typed anything, Recall shows **You keep coming back to** — the\npeople, sites, and files that recur across your days, each with how many days\nit spans and how many times you've seen it. Tap one to turn it into a search."],[450,"Beliefs about your focus"],[473,"Beliefs are derived directly from your history, not guessed by an AI, and every\none carries an honest confidence marker. A belief with thin evidence reads as\n&#x2A;*(tentative)*&#x2A; or &#x2A;*(likely)**; as the same person or file recurs across more\ndays, the belief is reinforced and its confidence grows. The strongest beliefs\nrise to the top of the Commonplace Book."],[145,"Both are derived from the same recurring-node snapshot the Second Brain's Network\ntab already shows: nodes are the things you keep returning to, and edges are the\nlinks between things that keep appearing together (weighted by how strong the\nconnection is)."],[117,"Both live under **Settings → Capture**."],[501,"Both write to your Mac and can be revealed in Finder; nothing leaves your\nmachine."],[80,"Bring data over from an older version of the app. Import is read-only on the\nsource — your originals are never touched — and never runs automatically."],[146,"By default both exports write inside Hindsight's own folder:"],[230,"By default Hindsight records two streams at once — your **microphone** and your\nMac's **system audio** (the other people on the call) — and keeps them as\nseparate, time-aligned tracks."],[54,"By default the CLI uses the app's shared database. Pass `--database <path>` on\nmost commands to point at a different one."],[68,"By default the result is saved to your library so it appears in the app."],[272,"By default, **journal entries are kept for 30 days** and then pruned. You can\nchange retention (7, 30, 90 days, or Forever) in the Colophon."],[15,"Calendar access is read-only and local: events stay on your Mac, and Hindsight\nnever uploads them. They're read fresh each time and never stored."],[1,"Calendar Auto-Start"],[41,"Calendar auto-start reads your events locally and acts on them locally. Nothing\nabout your calendar — titles, attendees, links, or times — ever leaves your Mac."],[39,"Calendar data never stops a recording. If a meeting runs long, Hindsight keeps\nrecording until you stop it yourself."],[123,"Capture and text recognition happen on-device, and nothing leaves your Mac\nunless you choose to connect an AI provider for the narrative or for chat."],[257,"Capture and transcription run entirely on your Mac. AI features — Ask, prompt\ntemplates, and auto-summaries — only reach out when you've connected a provider,\nand a local provider keeps everything on-device."],[8,"Changes apply right away"],[453,"Chat and recall"],[490,"Chat is the conversational home of the Second Brain. Ask it about your work — who\nyou keep dealing with, the files and tools you live in, or where your time\nactually goes — and it answers from what it has captured."],[497,"Chat, the Explain field, and drafting use an AI provider; the beliefs,\nInsights, and Network are computed locally and work without one. Connect a\nprovider under **Settings → AI Provider** — a local provider (Ollama, LM\nStudio) keeps everything on your Mac."],[505,"Checking manually"],[14,"Choose a **Calendar behavior** (see the modes below)."],[4,"Choose a behavior"],[231,"Choose the default for new recordings under **Settings → Audio sources**:"],[410,"Clearer day navigation."],[322,"Click any source to open that frame: the original screen, at the moment it was\ncaptured, so you can verify the answer with your own eyes. Every `[#N]` in the\nanswer maps to a row in the list."],[235,"Click the floating pill to open the meeting panel. The header shows whether\nyou're **Recording** or **Paused**, the elapsed time, and live level meters for\nthe microphone and system audio."],[42,"Command line"],[476,"Confidence only firms up once enough evidence has accumulated, and a belief\nthat earned trust keeps it."],[3,"Connect a calendar"],[254,"Continue the **chat** about it from the meeting's page."],[495,"Conversations are remembered: the Second Brain resumes your thread, keeps a\nrolling summary so long chats stay coherent, and can open a fresh chat when you\nwant one."],[88,"Day Journal"],[194,"Day Journal"],[353,"Day Journal"],[35,"Do nothing and recording starts automatically when the countdown ends."],[167,"Download the latest `Hindsight.dmg` from the\nReleases page."],[133,"Each completed day becomes a daily note, and the people, sites, and files you\nencountered become their own notes, joined together with `[[wikilinks]]` so the\nwhole thing browses as a connected web."],[286,"Each match is replaced inline with a placeholder like `[REDACTED:api_key]`. The\nmatched secret itself is never shown in the app and never leaves your Mac. The\nredaction pass is pure and offline — it makes no network calls of its own."],[58,"Each meeting also keeps **notes** and saved **results** (the output of prompts\nyou ran on it):"],[27,"Each reminder fires once per meeting. If your Mac is asleep or busy at the exact\nmoment, Hindsight still catches the reminder for a short window afterward so a\nlate tick won't make you miss it."],[470,"Each thing is tied back to the exact moment it appeared and timestamped, so it\ncan be ranked and shown without losing where it came from. Extraction runs\nentirely on your Mac on text that has already been redacted, so secrets such as\ncard numbers, keys, and one-time codes are never turned into entities. Ubiquitous\nplumbing — sign-in portals, analytics, CDNs, and boilerplate files like\n`README.md` or `package-lock.json` — is filtered out so it never looks like a hub\nof your work."],[277,"Every AI feature passes the same check before anything is sent: if no provider\nis configured the call is declined, a local provider is allowed, and a cloud\nprovider is allowed only with your consent. There is no separate path — journal\ntext, meeting transcripts, chat questions, drafts, and image descriptions all go\nthrough the same gate."],[53,"Every command accepts `--json` for clean, machine-readable output. Progress and\nstatus messages go to standard error, so the JSON on standard output stays\npipeable."],[498,"Everything stays on this Mac, and Export only materializes what you've already\ncaptured:"],[120,"Everything stays on this Mac, under your Library:"],[9,"Everything stays on your Mac"],[51,"Exit codes"],[124,"Export"],[454,"Export"],[127,"Export a graph"],[126,"Export an Obsidian vault"],[151,"Export is fully local. It reuses only the redacted, on-device data Hindsight\nhas already captured — secrets such as card numbers, keys, and one-time codes\nare never turned into notes — and nothing is sent anywhere. The files are yours\nto move, edit, and back up however you like."],[150,"Export needs something to materialize, so journal a few days first. If there's\nnothing to write yet, Hindsight tells you so rather than creating an empty vault."],[130,"Export turns what Hindsight has already captured into open, portable files you\ncan browse, link, and visualize in other tools. Nothing new leaves your machine\n— export only writes out the on-device, redacted data you can already see in the\napp. The database stays the source of truth; export is a one-way snapshot you can\nre-run any time."],[365,"Find any day in your history at a glance, and never lose one to an accidental delete."],[156,"First-time setup"],[407,"Fixes meeting transcription."],[294,"For a cloud provider, paste your **API key**. For a local provider, leave the\nkey blank."],[493,"For relational or temporal questions (\"how are X and Y connected?\", \"what have\nI been doing around Z?\"), it assembles real evidence from the graph and answers\nfrom that bundle, keeping `[#n]` citations so you can jump to the exact moment\neach claim came from."],[519,"Found a bug, or have an idea? Everything lives in one place:"],[472,"From that graph, Hindsight distills a self-model: a set of one-line **beliefs**\nabout you, each grouped by kind — people you keep dealing with, projects and\nareas of your work, topics that recur, tools and sites you live in, files you\nkeep returning to, rhythms in how you work, and open loops you touched then\ndropped."],[236,"From the header you can:"],[198,"Get started"],[152,"Getting started"],[448,"Getting to know you"],[163,"Granting Screen Recording on recent macOS"],[212,"Head to Getting started to install Hindsight, run\nfirst-time setup, and learn the three moves for turning through your book."],[32,"Higher-precision filters skip personal blocks and solo focus time. All-day\nevents and meetings you've declined are always skipped, whatever filter you\nchoose."],[114,"Hindsight can also pause on its own:"],[10,"Hindsight can watch your calendar so you never miss the start of a meeting. When\nan upcoming event matches your rules, Hindsight either drops a quiet reminder or\nopens a short, cancellable countdown and begins the minutes for you."],[509,"Hindsight checks for updates on its own, once a day by default. When a new\nversion is available it can download and install it for you, then apply it the\nnext time it is safe to do so."],[177,"Hindsight downloads and optimizes the speech model on this Mac so meetings can\nbe transcribed locally — **audio never leaves your machine**. You'll see a\nprogress bar while the model downloads and warms up. This is the one step you\ncan't skip: **Continue** stays disabled until the model reports\n&#x2A;*Speech model is ready.**"],[199,"Hindsight is a private daybook for your Mac. It is one continuous book you turn\nthrough, page by page: a **Day Journal** for what you worked on, **The Minutes**\nfor your meetings, and a **Second Brain** that learns from your history and can\ntalk it back to you."],[192,"Hindsight is a private, on-device daybook for macOS — a day journal, your meetings, and a second brain, all kept on your machine."],[266,"Hindsight is built to stay on your Mac. Capture, transcription, the knowledge\ngraph, and your whole journal database live locally, and nothing is sent to an AI\nunless you connect a provider and — for cloud providers — explicitly turn cloud\nanalysis on. This page explains exactly what stays put, what can leave, and how\nto control it."],[207,"Hindsight is on-device by default:"],[170,"Hindsight keeps itself up to date, and you can trigger a check yourself from the\nColophon under **The Apparatus → Check for updates**."],[518,"Hindsight never interrupts a recording to update. Update checks are paused while\na meeting is recording, and an already-downloaded update will not relaunch the\napp mid-recording. Stop the recording and the update can proceed — a manual check\nwill remind you if a recording is in progress."],[273,"Hindsight never talks to an AI provider unless you set one up:"],[52,"Hindsight ships with a companion command-line tool, `hindsight-cli`, that talks\nto the same database as the app. Anything you record, transcribe, or learn in\nthe app is visible from the terminal, and anything the CLI writes shows up in\nthe app. It is handy for scripting, exporting, and feeding your transcripts into\nother tools."],[508,"Hindsight updates itself. New versions download and install in the background, so\nyou generally do not need to do anything to stay current."],[43,"hindsight-cli is a companion tool that shares the app's database — list and export meetings, transcribe files on-device, manage speech models, inspect your Second Brain, and run LLM tasks from the terminal."],[503,"How Hindsight keeps itself up to date, how to check manually, and where to report problems."],[259,"How Hindsight keeps your data on-device by default, how optional cloud AI is gated by consent and redacted before it leaves your Mac, and where to configure a provider and keys."],[303,"How the answer is built"],[75,"How the key is resolved, in order: `--api-key` (a literal — discouraged), then\n`--api-key-env` (the name of an environment variable holding the key), then the\nconventional variable for the provider (for example `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`,\n`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`). Local providers like\n`ollama` need no key."],[517,"If a newer version exists, Hindsight shows you what changed and offers to install\nit. If you are already current, it tells you so."],[189,"If the Hindsight entry doesn't respond, remove it from the list and re-add\n`/Applications/Hindsight.app&#x60; with the &#x2A;*+** button, then relaunch."],[33,"If you have several calendars, expand **Calendars** to exclude specific ones —\na personal calendar, say, while keeping your work calendar. New calendars are\nincluded by default."],[323,"If you haven't connected a provider, Recall still works. Instead of prose, it\nreturns **cards** — each one a specific match (a phone number, an email, a\nlink, a file you saw) carrying the same time-and-place stamp, and a click opens\nthe frame it came from. Recording and search never need a provider; the answer\nstyle just changes."],[321,"If you've connected an AI provider, the answer streams back as prose, written\nonly from the days and frames that match your question. Under the answer is a\n**Sources** list. Each source is the exact frame the answer drew from, shown as\nits time, the app, and the window title — for example:"],[49,"Import"],[34,"In **Start recording automatically** mode, when a matching meeting begins\nHindsight opens a small countdown in the top-right corner. It shows the meeting\ntitle, the service name, and the attendee count, and counts down for 5 seconds."],[186,"In the setup step, press **Enable Day Journal** (or **Open System Settings**).\nThis adds Hindsight to the list and opens\n**System Settings → Privacy & Security → Screen & System Audio Recording**."],[331,"Inside a recorded meeting you can ask about that meeting on its own. Open the\nmeeting and use the &#x2A;*Ask about this meeting…** field to question its\ntranscript and your notes directly, without searching the rest of the book."],[451,"Insights"],[71,"Inspect the Second Brain self-model — what the app has learned about you — and\nverify it against the same guard the app uses, without opening the app."],[155,"Install"],[153,"Install Hindsight, run first-time setup, and grant Screen Recording on recent macOS."],[492,"It reads your question for what you're after (a phone number, a file, a site)\nand pulls the matching things from your journal."],[458,"It turns **Ready** once all four signals are met:"],[50,"JSON output"],[280,"JSON Web Tokens (JWTs)"],[95,"Keeping and clearing screenshots"],[61,"Key options:"],[5,"Lead time"],[2,"Let Hindsight watch your calendar and start your meetings for you — notify or auto-record, with everything staying on your Mac."],[48,"LLM"],[443,"macOS 14.2 or later."],[16,"macOS only asks for calendar permission once. If you decline, you can re-enable\nit later in **System Settings → Privacy & Security → Calendars**."],[69,"Manage the on-device speech models."],[125,"Materialize your knowledge as an Obsidian-style vault of linked Markdown notes, or as a knowledge graph in GraphML and Mermaid. Everything stays on your Mac."],[416,"Meeting recording now starts instantly."],[44,"Meetings"],[213,"Meetings"],[354,"Meetings"],[223,"Meetings is where Hindsight records, transcribes, and summarizes your\nconversations. Recording and transcription happen on-device. Each finished\nmeeting is saved alongside your days so you can revisit it later."],[216,"Microphone and system audio"],[46,"Models"],[318,"Move the selection with the up and down arrows, press Return to go,\nand Esc to dismiss — focus returns to the page you were on. The\nIndex is fast because it reads from what's already in memory; there's no\nwaiting."],[399,"Much better speaker detection, plus new ways to fix up a meeting after it's\nrecorded."],[452,"Network"],[425,"No feature changes — everything in 1.0.0 below is unchanged."],[431,"No feature changes — everything in 1.0.0 below is unchanged."],[28,"Not every calendar entry deserves a reminder. Under **Which events count**,\npick the filter that fits how you work:"],[83,"On failure in `--json` mode, the tool prints an error envelope instead of the\nnormal payload:"],[260,"On-device by default"],[356,"On-device by default"],[285,"One-time passcodes (OTPs)"],[141,"Only completed days are included, and every note is plain Markdown — no lock-in.\nRe-running the export refreshes the vault in place."],[169,"Open **Hindsight** from Applications."],[12,"Open **Settings → The Minutes → The Calendar**."],[521,"Open an issue there to report a problem or request a feature. When filing a bug,\nit helps to include the version you are on — you can find it in the **Colophon**\nunder **The Edition**, or in **Hindsight → About Hindsight**."],[456,"Open it from the Index (⌘K) and move between its four sections with\nthe tab bar or ⌘1–⌘4: **Chat**, **Insights**, **Network**,\nand **Export**."],[99,"Open the Day Journal control on today's page and press **Start**. The first time,\nmacOS needs the **Screen Recording** permission; grant it under\n**System Settings → Privacy & Security → Screen Recording**, then start again."],[168,"Open the DMG and drag **Hindsight** onto the **Applications** folder shortcut."],[317,"Open with an empty query and the Index shows a table of contents instead: the\nParts of your book, your three most recent days, your three most recent\nminutes, and the common commands."],[263,"Optional features that can send more"],[295,"Optionally set a **base URL** (for OpenAI-compatible endpoints this is\nrequired) and a **model**, or use **Refresh list** to pull available models."],[76,"Other useful options:"],[267,"Out of the box, everything happens on your machine:"],[82,"Pass `--json` to get stable, pretty-printed JSON with sorted keys and ISO-8601\ndates. Status text is kept off standard output, so you can pipe results\nstraight into other tools:"],[94,"Pausing capture"],[283,"Payment card numbers"],[293,"Pick a provider from **AI option** (or **None** to disconnect)."],[364,"Plus the usual polish: standardized section headings and spacing, a centered empty state on Meetings, and sharper accessibility labels."],[184,"Press **Open Hindsight** and you're in. You'll land on today's page in your\nDay Journal."],[113,"Press **Pause** during a session to stop new screenshots for a while. You can\nnote why with a quick reason — **Meeting**, **Break**, **Lunch**, **Personal** —\nor type your own. Press **Resume** to start capturing again. The pause (and its\nreason) is recorded, so a finished day can show when and why capture was\ninterrupted."],[296,"Press **Test Connection** to verify, then **Save**."],[309,"Press ⌘K from anywhere to open the Index. It is both a table of\ncontents and a search box for the whole book."],[183,"Press ⌘K once when prompted to summon the Index, then press\nReturn to finish."],[37,"Press Esc, click the toast, or hit the ✕ to cancel. That meeting\nwon't try again."],[36,"Press Return to start immediately."],[197,"Privacy"],[222,"Privacy"],[258,"Privacy"],[279,"Private keys"],[262,"Prompts are redacted before any cloud call"],[304,"Quick filters"],[89,"Quiet on-device screenshots, on-device text recognition, an AI write-up of your day, and an end-of-day review — all kept on your Mac."],[202,"Read more about the Day Journal →"],[204,"Read more about The Minutes →"],[206,"Read more about the Second Brain →"],[463,"Readiness is the weakest of the four, so a lopsided history (many frames but a\nsingle day) keeps warming until it fills out. Keep journaling and it gets there."],[299,"Recall"],[308,"Recall is how you ask your book a question and get a real answer back — built\nfrom what you actually saw and recorded, not from the open web. Two surfaces\nwork together: the **Index** for jumping straight to a page, and **Ask the\nBook** for questions that span many days at once."],[332,"Recall reads your own on-device book. Search and the deterministic card results\nstay entirely on your Mac. The streamed prose answer uses whatever AI provider\nyou've connected in the Colophon — and a local provider keeps everything on\nyour Mac for that too."],[214,"Record and transcribe meetings on-device, with a live panel, notes, and an AI Ask tab."],[434,"Record and transcribe meetings on-device. Start one from the Record tile, the\nmenu bar, the Index (**Begin minutes**), or the ⇧⌘M hotkey. Hindsight\ncan watch your calendar and offer to begin a recording when a meeting starts,\nrecognizing Google Meet, Zoom, and Microsoft Teams links."],[435,"Records your **microphone** and your Mac's **system audio** as separate,\ntime-aligned tracks (the default; **System Audio Only** is also available)."],[333,"Release notes"],[494,"Replies are checked against that evidence before they're saved, so a claim the\nhistory doesn't support is stripped out."],[154,"Requirements"],[357,"Requirements"],[253,"Run **prompt templates** against it — Summary, Action Items & Decisions,\nChapter Breakdown, and more."],[221,"Run a summary automatically"],[73,"Run language-model tasks from the terminal. Unlike the app, the CLI is\nconfigured per call — you pass the provider and key on each invocation; nothing\nis stored."],[437,"Saved meetings keep their transcript, notes, and any Ask conversation, and can\nbe renamed and re-run through prompt templates."],[118,"Screenshots are pruned automatically by the **Keep screenshots for** setting —\n**30 days** by default, or 7, 90, or Forever. Lowering it deletes older captures\non its next pass; \"Forever\" never auto-deletes."],[47,"Second Brain"],[196,"Second Brain"],[355,"Second Brain"],[446,"Second Brain"],[13,"Select **Grant Calendar Access**. macOS will ask for permission once."],[17,"Set **Calendar behavior** to one of three modes:"],[284,"Social Security numbers"],[215,"Start a recording"],[90,"Start capturing"],[310,"Start typing and it filters across everything in one place:"],[507,"Support and feedback"],[74,"Supported providers: `anthropic`, `openai`, `openaiCompatible`, `gemini`,\n`openrouter`, `ollama`, `lmstudio`, `omlx`, and `cli` (a local subprocess)."],[329,"Tap one to seed the search and see every matching moment."],[247,"The **Ask** tab lets you query an AI provider about the live transcript and your\nnotes without leaving the call. The empty state offers browsable quick prompts\ngrouped under **Catch Up**, **Capture**, and **Challenge** — for example\n\"Summarize so far\", \"Action items\", and \"What should I ask?\". Pinned follow-ups\nlike \"Tell me more\" and \"Counter-argument?\" sit above the input once a thread\nis going."],[480,"The **Insights** tab surfaces what's worth your attention right now, all derived\ndeterministically from your history:"],[484,"The **Network** tab is the graph at a glance:"],[84,"The `errorType` field comes from a small, stable vocabulary — for example\n`auth`, `config`, `connection`, `lookup`, `model`, `rate_limit`,\n`input_missing`, `input_empty`, and `validation` — so scripts can branch on the\nkind of failure."],[92,"The AI day narrative"],[324,"The Ask the Book view offers one-tap chips for the things people look for most:"],[7,"The countdown"],[38,"The countdown only appears when you're not already recording, and only for\nmeetings you've accepted or tentatively accepted (and your own untracked\nblocks). Meetings you haven't responded to won't auto-record, since recording an\nunaccepted meeting would be a surprise — but you can still get a reminder for\nthem."],[185,"The Day Journal and meeting recording both rely on the **Screen & System Audio\nRecording** permission. On recent macOS, granting it has one quirk worth knowing."],[201,"The Day Journal is today's page in your book — a running record of what you did,\nso you can reflect on your decisions later. Turn between days with the left and\nright arrows, and use **Ask the book** on any page to pose a question about your\nday or your history."],[98,"The Day Journal is today's page in your book. While it runs, Hindsight quietly\ntakes a screenshot of your front window every couple of minutes, reads the text\non screen so you can recall anything you saw, and — when you stop for the day —\nwrites the day up for you to review and keep."],[173,"The Day Journal periodically captures your screen and reads it with on-device\nOCR to weave a private narrative of your day. Screenshots never leave your Mac."],[378,"The Days page is also redesigned:"],[93,"The end-of-day review"],[432,"The first release of Hindsight: a private, on-device daybook for macOS. One\ncontinuous book you turn through page by page, with three pillars and an Index\n(⌘K) that jumps anywhere."],[171,"The first time you open Hindsight, it opens a first-run setup that walks you\nthrough a few short steps. A &#x2A;*Step *n* of *N*** counter sits in the top-right,\nand you can step back at any time with the chevron. Permission steps are\noptional and can be skipped with **Skip — I'll set this up later**; only the\non-device model step has to finish before you continue."],[218,"The floating pill"],[320,"The full Ask the Book view searches **anything you saw, across every day**.\nType a question — \"what was the address jane.smith sent me?\", \"which build\nbroke last Thursday?\" — and the book answers from your own captured history."],[301,"The Index: jump anywhere"],[449,"The knowledge graph"],[217,"The live panel"],[234,"The microphone **Mute** control is available only in Microphone + System Audio\nmode."],[175,"The microphone is **not** required for journaling — you can skip the next step\nand the Day Journal still works."],[176,"The microphone is only used for **meeting** capture. Grant it now if you plan to\nrecord meetings, or skip it and enable it later from the Colophon."],[195,"The Minutes"],[203,"The Minutes records and transcribes your meetings on-device. Start a recording\nfrom the Index or with ⇧⌘M; Hindsight can also watch your calendar\nand offer to begin minutes when a meeting starts, recognizing Google Meet, Zoom,\nand Microsoft Teams links. Finished meetings are saved to your Library with a\ntitle you can rename."],[110,"The narrative is the one part that draws on an AI provider. Connect one under\n**Settings → AI Provider** — a local provider keeps everything on your Mac.\nCapture, text recognition, search, and storage never need a provider."],[72,"The output lists each belief with its salience, confidence, and evidence count,\nand reports how many would be kept versus dropped by the current guard. Add\n`--include-inactive` to also show dormant or retired beliefs."],[240,"The panel has three tabs, switchable with ⌘1–⌘3:"],[70,"The Parakeet engine (`parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v3`) downloads automatically the first\ntime it is used, so `download` is only needed for `whisper`. Use `warm-up` to\nprepare an engine ahead of time (it may download on first run), and `clear` to\nremove cached models from disk."],[455,"The Second Brain is the Commonplace Book in Hindsight: the page that reflects\nyour own work back to you. It reads across every day you've captured, links the\nthings that keep recurring, and forms a small set of plain-language beliefs about\nwhat you focus on. You can read those beliefs directly, explore how everything\nconnects, and talk through your history."],[205,"The Second Brain learns from what you capture. Chat with your history, browse\nthe Insights it has noticed, explore the Network of how people, projects, and\nideas connect, and Export what you find — including drafting an email or a\ncalendar event from the conversation."],[374,"The Second Brain now answers from what your screens actually showed — not just who and\nwhat kept recurring."],[457,"The Second Brain only starts answering once it has seen enough of your work to be\nuseful rather than confidently wrong. The page shows where it stands — **Still\nlearning you**, **Getting to know you**, or **Ready** — with a progress bar and\nfour counts: days, frames, things, and threads."],[489,"The tab also offers a few starter questions; tapping one drops you into Chat with\nthat question already asked."],[193,"The three pillars"],[200,"The window is page-based. Turn left and right between days, jump anywhere with\nthe Index (⌘K), and let the red Ribbon bring you back to today.\nEverything you capture stays on this Mac."],[224,"There are three ways to begin:"],[496,"There's also an **Explain** field for two specific things — enter a person, file,\nor site on each side and Hindsight shows the shared bridges between them, drawn\nonly from your graph."],[287,"These are all **off by default** and each is independently controlled in the\nColophon:"],[178,"This download happens once. If a future launch already has the model cached, the\nstep finishes instantly. If setup stalls (for example, on a slow network), use\n**Retry**."],[11,"This is strictly opt-in. Until you connect a calendar and pick a behavior,\nHindsight ignores your calendar entirely."],[174,"This step asks for the **Screen & System Audio Recording** permission. Press\n**Enable Day Journal**, then toggle Hindsight on in the System Settings pane\nthat opens. The same grant also covers meeting recording later, so you only\ngrant it once. See Granting Screen Recording\nbelow if the status doesn't update right away."],[292,"To connect a provider:"],[104,"To wrap up, press **Stop & Review**. **Discard** throws the session away."],[45,"Transcribe"],[60,"Transcribe any audio or video file with the on-device speech engines. The file\nis decoded to audio and recognized locally — nothing leaves your Mac."],[513,"Turn either off if you would rather decide when to update."],[256,"Turn on **Run marked prompts automatically** under \"After each meeting\" to have\nchosen templates (the **Summary** template is marked by default) run as soon as\na meeting finishes. Because this sends the transcript to your AI provider, it's\noff until you switch it on. Use &#x2A;*Edit Prompts…** to add, pin, hide, or reset\nthe built-in prompts."],[412,"Turning the pages — fixed, and nicer."],[96,"Turning through your days"],[382,"Two fixes to the Second Brain."],[22,"Under **Remind me**, choose how far ahead you're nudged:"],[297,"Under **The Second Brain** in the same section you'll find the cloud consent\ntoggle (**Allow cloud AI to analyze your journal**) and the vision option; under\n**External Readers** you'll find the agent (MCP) toggles."],[491,"Under the hood, recall grounds every answer in your real history rather than\ninventing anything:"],[502,"Updates & Support"],[506,"Updates and your meetings"],[59,"Use `-` in place of text to read from standard input."],[119,"Use the left and right arrows to turn between days. The red Ribbon always brings\nyou back to today, and **Turn to today** is also available from the Index\n(⌘K, shortcut T)."],[191,"Welcome"],[334,"What changed in each version of Hindsight, newest first."],[91,"What gets captured"],[134,"What you get:"],[305,"What you keep coming back to"],[358,"What's new in Hindsight, newest first. Hindsight keeps itself up to date, and\nyou can check manually from the Colophon under **The Apparatus → Check for\nupdates**."],[471,"When two things keep appearing together, that co-occurrence becomes a link. The\nresult is a cross-day graph of who and what your work threads through."],[21,"When you pick a non-Off mode, Hindsight will ask for notification permission so\nreminders can appear. If notifications are turned off in System Settings,\nHindsight shows a warning with a shortcut to fix it."],[250,"When you press **Stop**, Hindsight transcribes the audio on-device and saves the\nmeeting to your **Recent meetings** list. The pill confirms with a checkmark and\nclears itself shortly after."],[229,"When you start, Hindsight checks for Microphone and Screen Recording access. If\neither is missing, it points you to System Settings. The first time, grant both\nso capture can run."],[319,"When you want an answer rather than a destination, ask the book. Open today's\npage and use the &#x2A;*Ask the book…** bar, or press ⇧⌘A from anywhere\nto jump there and start typing."],[128,"Where the files land"],[264,"Where to configure it: the Colophon"],[97,"Where your data is stored"],[265,"Where your keys are stored"],[6,"Which events count"],[244,"While a meeting is active, a small pill floats on top of every app. It pulses\nwith your audio levels while recording, dims with pause bars when paused, shows\na spinner while transcribing, and a checkmark when the meeting is saved."],[100,"While capture is running you'll see:"],[55,"Work with your saved meeting recordings and their transcripts."],[228,"You can also begin from the Index: ⌘K → **Begin minutes**."],[514,"You can look for a new version at any time:"],[479,"You can read all of this with no AI provider connected — the beliefs are\ncomputed locally and shown as cards."],[56,"You can refer to a meeting by its full ID, a unique ID prefix (at least four\nhex characters), or a unique title."],[190,"You can revisit any